HEADWORD: bosun
<hw>bosun</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a petty officer on a merchant ship who
controls the work of other seamen; a contraction of
<er>boatswain</er>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>bo'sun</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> boatswain, bos'n, bo's'n, bo'sun, boson.</syn>⟦br⟧
